many of our proposed changes.<br/><br/>We should also try to minimize potential merge conflicts between upstream (or an upstream we create) and the kissu.moe-specific branch. So for example, we\'d want to make sure configuration changes are in inc/instance-config.php as recommended and not in inc/config.php which might change upstream triggering a manual merge if we pull the changes. Perhaps we could add an inc/secrets.php file so we could publish our site configuration without publishing salts and passwords, sort of like how 8chan does:<br/><a href=\"https://github.com/OpenIB/OpenIB/blob/c0a94dd5d6bcb5ba5af82b2430ad69378adc90ab/inc/instance-config.php#L253\" rel=\"nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">https://github.com/OpenIB/OpenIB/blob/c0a94dd5d6bcb5ba5af82b2430ad69378adc90ab/inc/instance-config.php#L253</a><br/>And for another example, if we replace static/file.png as <a onclick=\"highlightReply(\'90\', event);\" href=\"/b/res/52.html#90\">&gt;&gt;90</a> suggested, instead of overwriting static/file.png we could create a static/kissu-file.png and add<br/>$config[\'file_icons\'][\'default\'] = \'kissu-file.png\';<br/>to inc/instance-config.php. That way if somebody changes static/file.png upstream, we don\'t have to manually resolve the merge.','Regarding this git stuff, it might be easier to have one local copy of the repo for development work which you\'d keep clean and another local copy for the website. And then you\'d pull changes from the clean development repo to the dirty website repo but generally not vice versa.\r\n\r\nAnd there should be separate branches for stuff we might send upstream or that might be useful on other sites versus customization specific to kissu.moe. vichan isn\'t very active lately but they seem to accept pull requests. We can fork and create our own upstream if they stop taking pull requests or if they disagree with too many of our proposed changes.\r\n\r\nWe should also try to minimize potential merge conflicts between upstream (or an upstream we create) and the kissu.moe-specific branch. So for example, we\'d want to make sure configuration changes are in inc/instance-config.php as recommended and not in inc/config.php which might change upstream triggering a manual merge if we pull the changes. Perhaps we could add an inc/secrets.php file so we could publish our site configuration without publishing salts and passwords, sort of like how 8chan does:\r\nhttps://github.com/OpenIB/OpenIB/blob/c0a94dd5d6bcb5ba5af82b2430ad69378adc90ab/inc/instance-config.php#L253\r\nAnd for another example, if we replace static/file.png as >>90 suggested, instead of overwriting static/file.png we could create a static/kissu-file.png and add\r\n$config[\'file_icons\'][\'default\'] = \'kissu-file.png\';\r\nto inc/instance-config.php. That way if somebody changes static/file.png upstream, we don\'t have to manually resolve the merge.\r\n',1543848936,1543848936,NULL,0,NULL,'hwE+OOes','73.223.119.89',0,0,0,0,NULL,NULL),(108,4,NULL,NULL,'Anonymous',NULL,NULL,'ｷﾀ━━━(ﾟ∀ﾟ)━━━!!','ｷﾀ━━━(ﾟ∀ﾟ)━━━!!',1543856208,1543856208,'[{\"name\":\"70873448_p0.png\",\"type\":\"image\\/png\",\"tmp_name\":\"\\/tmp\\/phpHS9j5z\",\"error\":0,\"size\":1076137,\"filename\":\"70873448_p0.png\",\"extension\":\"png\",\"file_id\":\"1543856207949\",\"file\":\"1543856207949.png\",\"thumb\":\"1543856207949.png\",\"is_an_image\":true,\"hash\":\"c8ddfec4451b98255aa011e1b7399b4a\",\"width\":925,\"height\":1346,\"thumbwidth\":175,\"thumbheight\":255,\"file_path\":\"b\\/src\\/1543856207949.png\",\"thumb_path\":\"b\\/thumb\\/1543856207949.png\"}]',1,'c8ddfec4451b98255aa011e1b7399b4a','6T_me10Gd','72.82.233.171',0,0,0,0,NULL,NULL),(109,1,NULL,NULL,'Anonymous',NULL,NULL,'<br/><a onclick=\"highlightReply(\'100\', event);\" href=\"/b/res/1.html#100\">&gt;&gt;100</a><br/>strange&hellip; did that here &gt;&gt;&gt;71','\r\n>>100\r\nstrange... did that here >>>71',1543860666,1543860666,NULL,0,NULL,'k6+2TjX2','24.157.164.104',0,0,0,0,NULL,NULL),(110,1,NULL,NULL,'Anonymous'