.82.233.171',0,0,0,0,NULL,NULL),(130,52,NULL,NULL,'Anonymous',NULL,NULL,'<a onclick=\"highlightReply(\'129\', event);\" href=\"/b/res/52.html#129\">&gt;&gt;129</a><br/>The consequences are really unforeseen if you don\'t say what they are','>>129\r\nThe consequences are really unforeseen if you don\'t say what they are',1543894080,1543894080,NULL,0,NULL,'4qkYDx3G','24.157.164.104',0,0,0,0,NULL,NULL),(131,52,NULL,NULL,'Anonymous',NULL,NULL,'<a onclick=\"highlightReply(\'130\', event);\" href=\"/b/res/52.html#130\">&gt;&gt;130</a><br/>For instance, I can\'t really think about what the positives would be aside from editing grammar. In which case just delete your post and redo it if you make that many fuck-ups. If people are allowed to edit their posts, I can see it being used in ways such as changing their original arguments slightly or in major ways to better suit them. It could also be used to cause all sorts of problems, such as fishing for a certain response, and then once you get that response edit your post to make the other person look like a jackass. It could also probably be used in ways to stealthily communicate links to CP, or hand out other things then edit out what they put in later. Or it could just be abused to allow people to be assholes in general.<br/><br/>Also I feel it sort of goes against the spirit of imageboards a little. You say what you say and it\'s here until you delete it, a mod deletes it, or the thread 404s/archives. Editing is better suited for platforms in which your words last forever.','>>130\r\nFor instance, I can\'t really think about what the positives would be aside from editing grammar. In which case just delete your post and redo it if you make that many fuck-ups. If people are allowed to edit their posts, I can see it being used in ways such as changing their original arguments slightly or in major ways to better suit them. It could also be used to cause all sorts of problems, such as fishing for a certain response, and then once you get that response edit your post to make the other person look like a jackass. It could also probably be used in ways to stealthily communicate links to CP, or hand out other things then edit out what they put in later. Or it could just be abused to allow people to be assholes in general.\r\n\r\nAlso I feel it sort of goes against the spirit of imageboards a little. You say what you say and it\'s here until you delete it, a mod deletes it, or the thread 404s/archives. Editing is better suited for platforms in which your words last forever.',1543894601,1543894601,NULL,0,NULL,'6T_me10Gd','72.82.233.171',0,0,0,0,NULL,NULL),(132,52,NULL,NULL,'Anonymous',NULL,NULL,'<a onclick=\"highlightReply(\'131\', event);\" href=\"/b/res/52.html#131\">&gt;&gt;131</a><br/><span class=\"quote\">&gt;Editing is better suited for platforms in which your words last forever.</span><br/>Or account-based systems. In which what you say reflects on you since people can trace the words back to you. When you\'re anonymous that shouldn\'t be something you need to worry about, or even consider because you\'re anonymous. Even if one adopts a trip that\'s their choice to be tied to said trip, so whatever they say they should be prepared to stick with it. And if you do happen to change your mind on something later, be it in a conversation or whole other thread, then just admit to having changed your mind.','>>131\r\n>Editing is better suited for platforms in which your words last forever.\r\nOr account-based systems. In which what you say reflects on you since people can trace the words back to you. When you\'re anonymous that shouldn\'t be something you need to worry about, or even consider because you\'re anonymous. Even if one adopts a trip that\'s their choice to be tied to said trip, so whatever they say they should be prepared to stick with it. And if you do happen to change your mind on something later, be it in a conversation or whole other thread, then just admit to having changed your 