','174.200.7.3',0,0,0,0,NULL,NULL),(24,NULL,'Fall 2018 Anime',NULL,'Anonymous',NULL,NULL,'Most of the shows I\'ve been watching this season have ranged from average to good, with the only real weak shows being the bunny girl one and Index s3 (could and has been improving slightly from the beginning). Think what I\'m going to look back on as the \'definitive\' anime this season will be Gridman, although that may be subject to change since I have yet to watch Karakuri Circus, Irozuku, and Thunderbolt Fantasy 2. At first I was almost certain that the hit of the season would have been Uzai Maid, but somehow it just sort of fizzled out. It\'s still good and all, but nothing that I\'m going to hail as great. Also for some reason most of the stuff I\'m really enjoying I\'d been holding off on for some reason, like Tonari no Kyuuketsuki and Golden Kamuy 2, which both are about as entertaining as Uzai Maid, if not moreso. If I were to make a list of shows that people should make an effort to watch from this season, it\'d probably include all of the prieviously mentioned good shows, along with Honda-san and Zombie Land Saga, with Yagate Kimi ni Naru if you like yuri.<br/><br/>So with that said, what are all your thoughts on the current season? Also did anyone watch FLCL Alternative, heard it was shit.','Most of the shows I\'ve been watching this season have ranged from average to good, with the only real weak shows being the bunny girl one and Index s3 (could and has been improving slightly from the beginning). Think what I\'m going to look back on as the \'definitive\' anime this season will be Gridman, although that may be subject to change since I have yet to watch Karakuri Circus, Irozuku, and Thunderbolt Fantasy 2. At first I was almost certain that the hit of the season would have been Uzai Maid, but somehow it just sort of fizzled out. It\'s still good and all, but nothing that I\'m going to hail as great. Also for some reason most of the stuff I\'m really enjoying I\'